CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June 9, 1945, pg. 8, reads: "Charming Ceremony - In a charming ceremony, performed in the home of the bride, last Wednesday, Miss Mary Beckett and Robert McEnheimer spoke their vows before a few relatives and friends. Shown in the wedding party are Mrs. Carry Jackson, matron of honor, the bride and groom, and best man, Dr. 'Bus' Cornelius. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Bride Mary Beckett McEnheimer wearing suit and orchid corsage, and groom Robert McEnheimer posed in Beckett home
